    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "7.06%"
} }
```

**Step-by-step calculation:**

### 1. Current Ratio
= Total Current Assets / Total Current Liabilities  
= 10,261,562.67 / 1,548,001.20  
= 6.63

---

### 2. Gross Profit Margin
= Gross Profit / Total Revenue  
= 2,620,023.09 / 5,760,023.09 ≈ 0.4548 = 45.48%

---

### 3. Debt to Asset Ratio
= Total Liabilities / Total Assets  
(From balance sheet, only current liabilities, no long term, so liabilities = current liabilities)
= 1,548,001.20 / 15,653,266.97 ≈ 0.0989 ≈ 0.10

---

### 4. Net Profit Margin
= Net Profit / Total Revenue  
= 1,105,265.77 / 5,760,023.09 ≈ 0.1920 = 19.20%

---

### 5. Cash to Current Debt Ratio
= (Cash on Hand + Bank Deposits) / Total Current Liabilities  
= (4,863,237.11 + 3,502,535.57) / 1,548,001.20  
= 8,365,772.68 / 1,548,001.20 ≈ 5.40

---

### 6. Free Cash Flow (FCF)
= Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities - Purchase of Fixed Assets  
= 803,237.11 - 437,464.43 = 365,772.68

---

### 7. Return on Assets (ROA)
= Net Profit / Total Assets  
= 1,105,265.77 / 15,653,266.97 ≈ 0.0706 = 7.06%
